I am looking for some T205s and I have some to trade as well.  Let me know if your looking for anything specific and if you have other variation cards.

Hi Cory,  I must confess - I don't really know the T205 market very well, but I have LOADS of them for sale at the moment: graded SGC and PSA HOF'ers, ML'ers, commons, and raw ones as well.  I've been putting a good assortment of PSA-graded on ebay, hoping to get a better feel for pricing - once this experiment is over, I'll start posting them for sale here.

As far as collecting them, I have all the ones that I want for now except for Collins (mouth open), and the extremely hard variations such as the Wilhelm, toughest Hoblitzell and the Matty 37-1.

If you have specific needs, please let me know and I'll work on getting those ready first.

I'm looking for the following:
T205 Wilhelm, Moran (extra line), A.P. Liefeld, Gaspar, Gray (Stats on back), Hoblizell (name correct, no cin), Daubert, Chase (extends)

[quote name="nutsonchin" post=947674]I'm looking for the following:
T205 Wilhelm, Moran (extra line), A.P. Liefeld, Gaspar, Gray (Stats on back), Hoblizell (name correct, no cin), Daubert, Chase (extends)[/QUOTE]

I have both Leifeld cards, Gaspar, Chase one ear, and the Hoblitzell.  I haven't inventoried all my T205's yet, so I'll have to see if I have anything else.

Unfortunately, I still don't have pricing info on any of the variations - slowly building a spreadsheet of pricing info, but completion is a long ways off.   

Example - I had one board member tell me the Wallace, no cap, 1 line is worth $100-200.  On the other hand, someone else mentioned paying over $500 for a lesser grade example.  My arms are up in the air.

vintagecardprices.com

this will save you a huge amount of research - and I think they have a 24 hour member ship for $4.

Best,
S


Also - Please let me know if you have any broad leaf, hindu, drum or blank backs.
